VeroRoute is a Qt-based application for designing and routing
stripboard (veroboard), perfboard, and simple 1- or 2-layer
PCB layouts. It automatically prevents short-circuits and checks
for open-circuits while you work, and can import netlists exported
from TinyCAD (Protel 1 format) and gEDA (Tango format) schematics.

This builds VeroRoute from its upstream source tarball using the
project's own qmake build and install rules.

At runtime VeroRoute writes user data (undo/redo history and any
custom part templates) under ~/.local/share/veroroute/.
